%N A393306 a(n) is the greatest number k that contains, in base n, every digit exactly once, and such that k/(n-1) (if n is even) or 2*k/(n-1) (if n is odd) is prime.
%C A393306 Every number that contains, in base n, every digit once is divisible by n-1 (if n is even) or (n-1)/2 (if n is odd).
%C A393306 Conjecture: a(n) exists for all n.
%H A393306 Robert Israel, <a href="/A393306/b393306.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..385</a>
%e A393306 a(4) = 201 because 201 = 3021_4 contains all digits 0 to 3 once in base 4, 201/(4-1) = 67 is prime, and no larger number works.
%p A393306 f:= proc(n) local b,p,x,i; uses combinat;
%p A393306       b:= `if`(n::even,n-1,(n-1)/2);
%p A393306       p:= lastperm(n);
%p A393306       do
%p A393306         x:= add((p[i]-1)*n^(n-i),i=1..n);
%p A393306         if isprime(x/b) then return x fi;
%p A393306         p:= prevperm(p);
%p A393306         if p = FAIL then return -1 fi
%p A393306       od;
%p A393306 end proc:
%p A393306 map(f, [$2..30]);
